:: addimage {"position":"1000,625","size":"100,100"}
To display an image, you can use standard HTML commands.

One easy way to get an image and the proper HTML command is to visit Wikipedia. 

I went to the 'climate' page and clicked on an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate#/media/File:ISS-48_Towering_cumulonimbus_and_other_clouds_over_the_Earth_(2).jpg" target="_blank">image</a>to get further information.

Do you see the more details button? Click that and then look for the 'Use this file' link. It should open a window to display the code you need to 'embed' the image in your TWINE project. Copy the whole code and drop it straight into your page. 

