:: changebackground {"position":"575,475","size":"100,100"}
When you are editing your TWINE page, notice that there is a menu of options above the edit box. This includes a multicolored icon. If you click on it and follow the dialogue options, it will construct a command that you can insert into your page that will change the background color.

If you want additional details on the commands, there is an <a "https://twine2.neocities.org/#macro_background" target="_blank">online manual</a>.

Note that the manual is not for TWINE specifically, but rather for the Harlowe storyformat, which is one of several different systems of commands that you can use in TWINE. I am quite fond of <a "https://www.motoslave.net/sugarcube/2/" target="_blank">SugarCube format</a>, which is another option for your projects.

